{
  "id": "quiz",
  "title": "Booleans Check",
  "description": "Comparisons, boolean variables, and `Boolean()` conversion.",
  "lessonId": "01.3.3-booleans",
  "graphIndex": "01.3.3",
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": "q1",
      "prompt": "What is printed for `age = 17`?\n\n```js\nconst canVote = age >= 18;\nconst isTeen = age >= 13 && age <= 19;\nconsole.log(canVote);\nconsole.log(isTeen);\n```",
      "options": [
        { "id": "a", "text": "`false` then `true`" },
        { "id": "b", "text": "`true` then `true`" },
        { "id": "c", "text": "`false` then `false`" },
        { "id": "d", "text": "`true` then `false`" }
      ],
      "correctOptionId": "a",
      "explanation": "17 is not `>= 18`, but it is a teen (13–19 inclusive)."
    },
    {
      "id": "q2",
      "prompt": "What is printed for `score = 90`?\n\n```js\nconst passed = score >= 60;\nconst perfect = score === 100;\nconst invalid = score < 0 || score > 100;\nconsole.log(passed);\nconsole.log(perfect);\nconsole.log(invalid);\n```",
      "options": [
        { "id": "a", "text": "`true`, `false`, `false`" },
        { "id": "b", "text": "`true`, `true`, `false`" },
        { "id": "c", "text": "`false`, `false`, `true`" },
        { "id": "d", "text": "`true`, `false`, `true`" }
      ],
      "correctOptionId": "a",
      "explanation": "90 passes, is not perfect, and is in valid range."
    },
    {
      "id": "q3",
      "prompt": "What is the result of `Boolean(\"\")`?",
      "options": [
        { "id": "a", "text": "`false`" },
        { "id": "b", "text": "`true`" },
        { "id": "c", "text": "`\"\"`" },
        { "id": "d", "text": "`undefined`" }
      ],
      "correctOptionId": "a",
      "explanation": "Empty string is falsy. `Boolean(\"hello\")` would be `true`."
    },
    {
      "id": "q4",
      "prompt": "What does `score >= 60` return when `score` is `85`?",
      "options": [
        { "id": "a", "text": "`true` (a boolean)" },
        { "id": "b", "text": "`85`" },
        { "id": "c", "text": "`\"true\"`" },
        { "id": "d", "text": "`1`" }
      ],
      "correctOptionId": "a",
      "explanation": "Comparison operators always produce `true` or `false`."
    },
    {
      "id": "q5",
      "prompt": "For `raw = \"   \"`, what is `isEmpty`?\n\n```js\nconst trimmed = raw.trim();\nconst isEmpty = trimmed.length === 0;\n```",
      "options": [
        { "id": "a", "text": "`true`" },
        { "id": "b", "text": "`false`" },
        { "id": "c", "text": "`undefined`" },
        { "id": "d", "text": "`null`" }
      ],
      "correctOptionId": "a",
      "explanation": "Whitespace-only input trims to empty string, so `length === 0` is `true`."
    }
  ]
}
